** Join Our Thriving Team as a Senior Project Engineer! **

Are you passionate about managed IT and driving success for partners? Our
dynamic team is looking for a talented Senior Project Engineer to lead the way
in delivering our technology projects. This is a unique opportunity to work
closely with our partners, ensuring their projects are completed to the
highest standards of satisfaction.

The role encompasses elements of pre-sales, technical project coordination,
and project execution, aimed at supporting our Managed Services Partners. As a
Project Engineer, you will organise your schedule to include client
consultations, project planning, and the management of several projects
simultaneously.

** Lead Our Project Team to Success **

  * Develop, manage, and execute project plans, ensuring tasks, milestones, and resources are effectively aligned. 
  * Work closely with the Technical Services Manager to manage both partner and internal projects. 
  * Enhance partner satisfaction through excellent project delivery and continuous improvement efforts. 
  * Serve as a trusted advisor to partners, guiding them towards desirable outcomes. 
  * Ensure project objectives are clear, coordinating with the team to deliver projects that meet our quality assurance standards. 
  * Drive problem resolution, manage risks, and ensure projects are delivered successfully. 
  * Design and maintain project documentation, identifying and managing any out-of-scope work. 
  * Support our sales team with accurate quoting and budget management. 

** Are You Up for the Challenge? **

** To excel in this role, you should possess the following skills and attributes: **

  * Bring at least 5 years of Senior Project and/or Help Desk Support experience to the table. 
  * Proven ability to work within a team and communicate effectively. 
  * Commitment to take ownership of projects and deliver results. 
  * Experience with project management tools like ConnectWise and Cognition 360. 
  * Tackle Microsoft Exchange Server 2016/19 and master Office 365 Implementation and management. 
  * Familiarity with 3CX Phone System highly regarded. 
  * Microsoft Certifications? They'll be highly regarded, too. 
  * A proactive approach to problem-solving and risk management. 
  * Excellent organisational skills, able to manage daily, weekly, monthly, and quarterly tasks efficiently. 
  * Keen attention to detail with the ability to document processes and ensure all partner documentation is current. 

** Why Join Us? **

  * Be part of a supportive and collaborative work environment. 
  * Opportunity to make a significant impact on our partner's success. 
  * Continuous learning to stay abreast of the latest technologies. 

** What Sets You Apart: **

  * Provide exemplary customer service, setting a high standard for all levels of the company. 
  * A flexible, self-motivated, and pro-active attitude with an unwavering attention to detail. 
  * Engage directly with partners to discuss and resolve project issues. 
  * Lead your project team with integrity, ensuring smooth operation and effective communication. 

  
** Why Choose Davichi Computer Services? **

  * A challenging yet rewarding role with direct impact on project success. 
  * A supportive team environment where your contributions are truly valued. 
  * An opportunity to grow and develop your project management skills in a tech-focused company. 
